TEHRAN, Oct. 20 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Ministry of Foreign Affairs strongly condemned the deadly terrorist attack in Syria's capital Damascus on Wednesday. Saeed Khatibzadeh, spokesman for the ministry, expressed sympathy for the families of the victims, according to the ministry's official website. Khatibzadeh said such act cannot undermine the determination of the Syrian government and the people in the fight against terrorism and the liberation of occupied territories of the country. At least 14 people were killed and two others wounded in a bomb attack on an army bus in central Damascus on Wednesday. Enditem